28/11/2002
TIRANA, Albania -- Chief prosecutor Theodhori Sollaku met his Italian counterpart Piero Luigi Vigna on Wednesday (27 November) to discuss joint efforts for fighting organised crime, trafficking and prostitution. The Italian delegation pledged to help prosecutors in Albania maintain an archive for identification of criminals. Participants agreed that co-operative efforts have already contributed to a significant decline in human trafficking. (ATA, OSCE web site - 27/11/02)
